The 3-layer design doesn’t block breathability, but helps block pollen and dust. Breathable material is more comfortable for little ones to wear.

body.description: Nuby kid face mask will help you and your little one enjoy your time outdoors, sneeze-free. High pollen count means lots of sneezing and less fun while playing outdoors.Each mask is made of soft, breathable fabric and comes in colorful patterns and fun designs. The built-in, bendable nose clip makes it easy to adjust the mask to fit your child's face. Our masks are made to fully cover your child's nose and mouth, providing more thorough protection. Soft ear loops make the mask comfortable for longer wear, keeping little ears from hurting. Nuby kid face masks aren't only for outdoor use, either! The masks can be used indoors when doing chores to avoid sneezing and irritation caused by dust and dirt. PLEASE NOTE: PER INTERNATIONAL REGULATIONS, DR. TALBOT’S IS REQUIRED TO INCLUDE AN EXPIRATION DATE ON PACKAGING. THIS DATE DOES NOT REFLECT THE EFFICACY OF THE MASKS. DR. TALBOT’S FACE MASKS DO NOT EXPIRE.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are the best fitting masks I’ve found I’ve found for 2 year old!
reviews.reviewText: I never leave reviews but I have to for this product! My daughter is two (born winter of 2018) and I have had the hardest time finding masks that fit her. I feel as if I’ve tried literally everything and it’s a constant struggle to keep the mask from riding up into her eyes, or coming off one ear, or both! It’s so annoying to having to manually make loops on standard kids masks for each side of the mask to make it fit tight enough to prevent it from not falling off completely. These masks fit flawlessly! Best masks I’ve found! No weird order, they don’t break, and best of all: my daughter loves them and finds them comfortable! There is not a single thing I can find to dislike. They are great for toddlers who chewOn masks or get them wet when wearing as well because they’re disposable! I think part of the reason for a toddler messing with their mask is that theyDon’t fit properly and in a time of Covid proper mask wearing is not something I’m willing to mess around with when out or around others with my daughter. I would recommend these masks to any parent and I think I ideally they fit age 2-4

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally, one that made it through the hole day without the ear loops ripping off!
reviews.reviewText: The only brand so far for little ones that we've found of amazing quality are the Halyard ones, but they're impossible to find, since they mostly equip hospitals. I've tried other kids ones and they are all uncomfortable, too big, and the ear loops tear right off almost immediately! Just Play makes a great smaller-sized mask but they are ridiculously expensive. I decided to try these because I found out Dr. Talbot's are manufactured by Nuby, a brand I've trusted for over 9 years. They are AWESOME! My 9 and 5 year old were able to make it through the entire 8 and 9 hour school days in them without the loops tearing off, and with them fitting perfectly on both of their faces! Even my 9 year-old, who is very tall for his age fits the size small better then the other brands. I recommend these for parents who are trying to keep their kids safe all day long.
